cle heal he cent while I fought him, figuring it'd prolong the battle. Then, um, somebody killed the oracle. Not that I'm complaining. But there has to be a better way, no? <br><br>Lest <br>competent swordsman, but batting .128 with a mace...  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usmallcutepuppy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smallcutepuppy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 134<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/15/02 10:36:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish I kept that rusty two-hander</span><hr size=1> Get in a group that doesn't mind having to heal you more because your weapons skills suck, or get in a group where you're not the main tank, and the rest of them don't mind you outputting less damage due to your skills sucking. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugorebloodlust.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gore Bloodlust</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.jjentertainmentnetworks.com/users/smilies/rock.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dead Sexy Leezard</span><br>  Posts: 259<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/15/02 10:46:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.ecomplanet.com/VEUX1804/ServerContent/MyCustomImages/VEUX1804CustomImage0376924.gif width=68 height=146></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish I kept that rusty two-hander</span><hr size=1> If your a warrior, don't worry about 2 hand weapons. Just work on one handers, stick what ever you want to work on in your off hand and it will go up, while you still do good dmg with main.<br><br>2 hand weapons are for those who can not duel wield.<br><br>Don't waste yourself. <p><br>Gore Bloodlust<br>57th Iksar Warrior ( Dead Sexy )<br>Proud member of Fire & Fury<br><a href="http://www.clicksmilie.de" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.clicksmilie.de/sammlung/waffen/waffen089.gif" border="0"></a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utirgaswiftpaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tirga swiftpaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/15/02 12:02:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://technuhemera.hypermart.net/newspro/Portrait.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish I kept that rusty two-hander</span><hr size=1> Gore's got it pretty much downright... I would still practice it a bit if you can... use skill points up to where it will cost you a plat to raise it. (those skill points are there for a reason ya know... I got 100+ <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>2 handed weapons are pretty cheep now... kill some willowisps and buy a decent on a 20/42 goes for about 40pp, that's 4 willowisps (greater lightstones to South Karanas) if you get a good weapon then it will ballance out with you low skill (so it will seem like you are still contributing)<br><br>I never had much of a problem with it... of course I am a bard and no one rely's on MY melee damage, just songs...<br><br>Trying to concentrate on upping all your weapon types is a good idea... hard work but will open up a lot of doors for you in the future.<br> <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112298">Tirga Swiftpaw</a> <br> Bard of 36 Compositions</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lest>Lest</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/15/02 1:00:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> RE:</span><hr size=1> Thanks. I stumbled onto a magic 1HS last night for the first time so I'll finally be able to hunt some wisps and put some money in the bank... <br><br>As a ranger I've been sticking to 1H weapons in anticipation of dual wield, but my mind keeps going back to an online guide I read once that said, roughly, &quot;There's nothing sadder to watch than a high level character trying to work up his Feeble melee skill so he can use that new weapon he just found...&quot; <br><br>Lest<br>lead singer for Feeble City Blues <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utirgaswiftpaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tirga swiftpaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/15/02 1:04:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://technuhemera.hypermart.net/newspro/Portrait.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:</span><hr size=1> Aye...very true... I can sell you some decent 1hs 1hb and peirce weapons for cheep if you need em... I need some space (you can check the market forum I'll let you have a discount ~ a good discount)<br> <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112298">Tirga Swiftpaw</a> <br> Bard of 36 Compositions</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ueyston.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eyston</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/16/02 3:43:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish I kept that rusty two-hander</span><hr size=1> While I agree with Gore, I do think it is fun to be proficient in all weapon skills.<br><br>Anyways, don't worry too much about maxing out skills right now.  Get the best primary weapons you can afford.  Max out skills later in life when a level takes more than a few hours.  Putting something in your offhand won't really make you completely worthless.  You figure about 70-80 percent of your damage is from the primary.<br><br>-=Viren=- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 222<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/16/02 4:43:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish I kept that rusty two-hander</span><hr size=1> You DO need 2h skills.  Why?  Because in raids, you may not be the main tank.  So have fun with a two hander.  <br><br>Just get a nice low delay weapon and have a little fun.  Low delay is relative with two handers of course...<br><br>Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalninil>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 282<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/16/02 5:16:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish I kept that rusty two-hander</span><hr size=1> you need 2h to joust with nothing worse than finding out you're out of pumice/wand while someone still has there DS up. very painful. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urhatha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhatha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Khati Sha</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/19/02 5:20:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://darklance.freewebspace.com/images/rhatha.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish I kept that rusty two-hander</span><hr size=1> Keep them all maxed at every level possible, it's that simple.  I did a fair job, but even now with 2HB at 134, it's a pain to raise.  No matter what anyone says, just find a decent weapon of each type and use em.  In the long run, you'll be glad you did. <p>-----------------------------<BR><A HREF='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112438' target=new>Rhatha Sha`Naya</A> and Swiftclaw<BR>40th season Khati Sha and Warder<BR><A HREF='http://darklance.freewebspace.com/index.ht